paladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> Monks are killers on damage your gona find it hard to keep agro no matter what. Only thing I can say is stun's so your gona need to med.<br><br>BTW In my exp I have found 2hs gets more agro. <p><center><img src="http://members.rogers.com/keter7036/roper01.jpg"></center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120412">My Magelo Profile</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uropertruson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roper Truson</A> at: 5/27/02 1:54:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 5:31:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> While I think a 1hs might have somewhat higher taunt value, you'd probably be giving up some significant damage by switching.<br><br>If you're using your whole taunting toolbox, I would think you could grab aggro.<br><br>One thing in particular that might help your situation would be getting a Deepwater bracer.  Mana free stuns might help you keep aggro without having to med.  With its rather long cast time you might lose some damage there as well, but aggro certainly won't be a problem if you're chain casting it and with a nice heavy 2hs you'll still get some swings in between casts.<br><br>Root is also good--if you root and hug the mob you *will* have aggro until root breaks.  Otherwise, I'd probably use cease/desist since they are low mana.  Depending on the situation you could also throw in Flash of Light since it's low mana as well, you just need to watch out if there's a chance the mob could run off and start a train, but in a full group situation that's unlikely.  You might also make a Taunt social macro that includes disarm for whatever extra bit of taunt it adds.<br><br>Back when I got my DW bracer I did my first OS group with a monk pulling and I was chain casting the bracer.  It kept the froggies stunned for about half the time (in effect it was like slowing the mobs), the casters rarely got a spell off, and aggro never left me.  Getting and keeping aggro from a monk is not hard. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvarutiasilvon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varutia Silvon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 5:35:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> use a high damage 2hs works best for me. Chuck in some quick stuns and hug the mob real close, they will stick to you like honey, except in rare circumstance.<br><br>You kill them quicker by doing more damage as well.<br> <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=177561>Varutia Silvonesit </a><BR>Level 56 Knight<BR>Terris Thule</center><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggorsmortus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RiggorsMortus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/smiley.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 354<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 6:26:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.standonguard.com/images/m_gordie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> hmm, maybe monk should FD more? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwulf9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulf9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 444<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 9:44:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> Puller is always going to have abnormally high aggro as the first person on aggro list.<br><br>If you have no mana regen and you're chain pulling so you dont have the mana to use your taunt spells to the full.. just share aggro with the monk and let them do some tanking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiseheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iseheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 10:07:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> Your best bet is to work out a system where the monk stays FD long enough for you to get aggro, and KEEP it. While a paladin can duo well with a monk, providing buffs, heals, and 'tanking ability' to go with the monk's damage output, you will not be able to keep up with the monk's support requirements (heals, buffs, and stuns for aggro) without doing a bunch of medding.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uennder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennder</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 10:51:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> answers</span><hr size=1> Probably need the damage output of a 2h to keep taunt.  Spam cease and disist to help, both are cheap on the mana bar and do a good job taunting.  <br><br>Definetly get divine might asap, that will help with your taunting as it gives you more procs which are generally good taunters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udivesufferhead.showPublicProfile?language=EN>divesufferhead</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 12:11:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: answers</span><hr size=1> dont taunt and let him aggro.. if he gets sick of it he will fd and you can gain aggro..... he has to work WITH you for you to gain aggro without spending mana<br><br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=166217">Dive Sufferhead</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umysthawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mysthawk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 1:47:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: answers</span><hr size=1> Just so you know, monks can tank very well, experience mobs that is.<br><br>Just because the monk is doing a little tanking isn't a bad thing.  If the monk isn't getting chewed up, then you probably don't need to try and force yourself into the tanking role.<br><br>Of course it goes both ways, the monk has to know when to FD to clear himself of his argo too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><hr width="40%"><b>Skorle Thedrifter</b> - 60 Iksar GrandMaster <img src="http://www.vbforums.com/images/smilies/cool.gif"><br>Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uradiation911.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Radiation911</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 2:42:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blizzard.com/images/war3/units/dreadlord.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: answers</span><hr size=1> It depends on the monk's equipment, if it's similar to yours as far as AC/HP wise then who cares, long as someone is taking damage then it's all good. Go pull if you're not tanking.<br><br>It also depends if there is a cleric in the group that is CHing, if he is then to make CH more efficient you're better off taking the hits as you'll most likely have more HPs. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3088>Radiation Contamination</a><BR>Crusader of Truth<BR><a href=http://www.planeteverquest.com/cazicthule>Cazic Thule Server</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaelyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 4:52:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: answers</span><hr size=1> Use low cost stuns as much as possible.  I typically land Stun and Holy Might at the start of the fight, and have little trouble holding aggro for the rest of the fight.<br><br>That is, of course, if the other parties in the fight practice good aggro control skills.  If they aren't, then you will definitely have to fight to keep aggro. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113786>Aelyn</a> <BR>53rd Cavalier of Tunare<BR><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=199555>Abydos</a><BR>40th Wizard</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 1396<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 5:59:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> On the discussion of agro from weapons it is from doing damage to the monster.  So you should choose to use the weapon that does more DPS if you want to gain more agro.<br><br>But in general relying on weapon performance is a poor way to control agro.  After all you can miss a lot on a &quot;high agro weapon&quot; and you've not done your taunting job.<br><br>Instead work with your Monk friend.  Have him right when he gets back to you and in agro range FD.  Feign Death is one of the best ways to dump agro in the game.  Without another target the monster should agro onto you easier.<br><br>In the course of the fight if the Monk is still gaining agro he need to toss in an FD more.  Or you can adjust your strategy and use more of your &quot;Taunt Tools&quot;.  Your entire Stun Line is not only one of the best ways to gain agro but one of the best ways to stop the monster to allow whoever a chance to escape(ie. the monster is pounding on them a well placed stun will allow the FD to slip through the hits and work).<br><br>It is all part of the game.  Your Monk friend has to learn to control their run away agro.  You have to learn to tweak the monsters in just such a way to hold that agro.  Keep practicing and you'll figure it out. ^_^ <p><font size="+1">Aeka<br>Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br><font color="#cc00cc">Just don't ask about the purple hair</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleifelf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leifelf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 1012<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 9:30:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> A couple stuns and a taunt and your gonna get aggro.  I never have trouble getting aggro.<br><br>Thats one of the coolest things about Paladins - We can control our aggro.<br><br>You want aggro off, just root and back off.  you want aggro on, just stun.  <br><br>It works.<br> <p>Leifelf <BR>59 Knight <BR>Bristlebane Server <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 919<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/02 10:15:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Flash of Light</span><hr size=1> Problem solved.<br><br>Although some things in Luclin, like underbulks dunnae seem ter care aboot being blind. Mayhap they dunnae have eyes?<br> <p>Wulfhere Hausakliufr<BR>Hammer o Brell, Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udigrenkaellise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DigrenKaellise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/28/02 9:18:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flash of Light</span><hr size=1> <br>With a monk and myself as the only melee on a Kael raid yesterday, I was able to hold aggro without much difficulty.  (The necro even announced that, with a Paladin tank, his damage output was doubled since he wasn't drawing aggro if he double stacked dots and chain nuked.)  I was using my Nature's Defender.<br><br>Halfway through the raid a Defiance dropped, 9/19 1HS.  I switched to it and a shield for the remainder of the raid.  While I was able to hold aggro with either weapon, I found I could stun less and keep aggro with the faster 1HS.  Of course my damage output also suffered some.<br><br>So I'll keep the Defiance for when I'm MA.  I'll also use it in places like HoT.  I've had problems there with my Nature's Defender taking aggro from the warrior MA if I get two quick procs, which seems to happen 1-2 times each raid.  With the 1HS I can also use a resist shield which will help me there too. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43978">Digren Kaellise</a><br>Knight of Tunare<br><a href="http://www.childrenofthephoenix.org">< Children of the Phoenix ></a><br><a href="http://www.tunareguildalliance.org/">Tunare Guild Alliance</a><br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kleitus>Kleitus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mcs.kent.edu/~rheath/Kleitus_pics/kleitus-small2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 735<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/28/02 10:32:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mcs.kent.edu/~rheath/Kleitus_pics/kleitus-small2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flash of Light</span><hr size=1> I think your best bet (since I'm assuming this is in just a pure exp grind spot) is to root the mob and be the closest one to it.  Make sure your monk knows you're going to be doing this and that he attacks from the opposite side of you (so he doesn't get reposted) and you can judge how close you need to be.  <br><br>I do this with a rogue fairly often and it works great.  Both of those classes CAN tank exp mobs just fine if need be (though you never want the rogue to have to give up his backstabs).  The one thing going against the monk as a tank vs. the pally is the higher number of fast attacks.  They just have alot more chances to be reposted and beaten around - their high defense makes up for it some but I'd rather not worry about it and have them attack from the other side of me.<br><br>If you can't root the creature (alot of the shrooms in FG are a pain to root) then use cease/desist and flame of light (its got a lot of taunt associated with it and does a bit o' damage too) plus taunt to keep it on you.  Sure the monk will take a few slaps here and there but thats to be expected and its a monk, so they can take the beating too.<br><br>I use two handers almost exclusively and I don't have a problem. <p>Kleitus <br>Level 54 Deepwater Cavalier of Erudin <br>Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usodas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sodas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/28/02 10:52:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flash of Light</span><hr size=1> You want to gain aggro? 3 Things u can do<br><br>get a weapon with a proc<br>get a weapon with high DPS<br>use Cease/Desist<br><br>DW Bracer is worthless for taunt, the 6 or 7 secs you cast stun makes u swing less during that time, making you lose aggo.<br><br>Flash of Light is okie, but time and time again, i've found it not nearly enough aggro for me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uamandilfuryfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amandil Furyfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/28/02 10:59:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> <br>As a monk I usually FD after pulling so the tank gets the aggro.   Remembers also that monks get Mend every 6 minutes which heals 25% of hitpoints.  So I will sometimes not FD at once, keep fighting and use Mend once HP goes down to 70%.  Monks also have good avoidance which helps them get hit less often.<br><br>I think in short don't worry about monk health.  If he can keep fighting the quicker the fight will end <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><BR><center><img src=http://amandil.netfirms.com/amandil22.jpg></center><BR><center><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=219998" TARGET="_NEW">Amandil's Equipment</A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucdarz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cdarz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/28/02 7:50:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.veilofshadows.org/modules/egallery/gallery/misc/vossmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question about taunting</span><hr size=1> Journeyman's walking stick is all I have to say. Cheap and fairly fast, and the proc is hella aggro. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64848>Cdarz Sanae</a><br>Knight of -<a href=http://www.veilofshadows.org>Veil of Shadows</a>-<br>Citizen of Luclin<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaliewin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taliewin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 292<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/28/02 11:15:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15691.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 2H seem to be better</span><hr size=1> Unless you have some really fast one hander, high damage two handers seem to be better for taunting, although the better the DPS the better the taunt obviously.<br><br>Also consider haste, how much haste does the monk have compared to you? If it is greater than you then your chances of keeping agro are diminished, as monks already put out so much damage without haste to gain a lot of agro.  I can keep agro pretty well even against monks but then I have RBB <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . (once came in on a fight in frenzy waiting for a spot to open in group, when frenzy was at two thirds life I engaged and by half life I had gained agro and kept it from a monk, ranger, warrior and paladin, most higher than me in level <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br><br>As many have said here if he has similar AC and HPs to you then don't be too bothered, and remember it is just as much his job to keep agro under control as it is yours.<br><br>If stuns aren't working as was pointed out root can be helpful.  Root the mob then get in its face, and while root lasts it will only attack you if you are the closest to it. Also if it is safe to use and you can keep close enough to it flash of light is big agro. A lot of people also tie in disarm to their taunt key as it is supposed to be of some agro gaining value as well.  And if you can, pull yourself instead of him unless there needs to be FD pulling or something like that.<br><br>If you are wasting too much mana over it I would say just do what you can while being as efficient as possible. It may mean and (without being nasty) force the monk to work on things from his side as well. It may also not be essential for you to hold agro all the time.<br><br><br>Taliewin Lifesworde<br>Half Elven Paladin of the 52nd Rank<br>Fellowship of Trust<br>Mith Marr Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topic